# Dockerfile-specific ignore patterns for expense-agent-svc.
# Docker BuildKit reads this file when building with
# `docker build -f expense-agent-svc/Dockerfile .` from repo root.
#
# All paths are relative to the repository-root context, so the
# entries below reach into every sibling project we might otherwise
# accidentally copy in.

# Version control + local dev
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# Node / TypeScript builds (expense-web is not needed inside the agent image)
expense-web
**/node_modules
**/dist
**/build
**/coverage
**/.next
**/.turbo

# Java (expense-api is not needed inside the agent image)
expense-api

# Python caches / venvs
# Explicit + glob patterns — the top-level `.venv` alone was not
# always caught by `**/.venv` in some BuildKit versions.
.venv
expense-ai/.venv
expense-mcp-server/.venv
expense-agent-svc/.venv
**/.venv
**/venv
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache
**/.mypy_cache
**/.ruff_cache
**/.coverage
**/htmlcov
**/coverage.xml
**/.tox

# Local environment / secrets — must never enter the image.
**/.env
**/.env.*
!**/.env.example
**/*.pem
**/*.key
**/*.p12
secrets/

# Docs / editor noise
# NOTE: hatchling reads the `readme` field of each pyproject.toml at
# build time. expense-agent-svc / expense-mcp-server use README.md;
# expense-ai uses PYTHON.md. Keep both classes.
**/*.md
!**/README.md
!**/PYTHON.md
**/.vscode
**/.idea
**/.DS_Store

# Precomputed reports / evidence
**/docs/evidence/**/*.log
